Bayesian Prior Sensitivity Analysis — ETNO ϖ Clustering
======================================================================
  N = 19, R_obs = 0.5052

--- (a) Uniform priors: κ ~ U(0, κ_max) ---
  U(0,  1):  BF₁₀ = 8.9  log₁₀BF = 0.95
  U(0,  2):  BF₁₀ = 11.5  log₁₀BF = 1.06
  U(0,  3):  BF₁₀ = 7.9  log₁₀BF = 0.90
  U(0,  5):  BF₁₀ = 4.7  log₁₀BF = 0.68
  U(0, 10):  BF₁₀ = 2.4  log₁₀BF = 0.37

--- (b) Half-Normal priors: κ ~ HN(σ) ---
  HN(σ= 0.5): BF₁₀ =      6.3  log₁₀BF = 0.80  [moderate]
  HN(σ= 1.0): BF₁₀ =     10.0  log₁₀BF = 1.00  [strong]
  HN(σ= 2.0): BF₁₀ =      7.9  log₁₀BF = 0.90  [moderate]
  HN(σ= 5.0): BF₁₀ =      3.7  log₁₀BF = 0.56  [moderate]
  HN(σ=10.0): BF₁₀ =      1.9  log₁₀BF = 0.27  [moderate]

--- (c) Exponential priors: κ ~ Exp(λ) ---
  Exp(λ=0.5): BF₁₀ = 6.8  log₁₀BF = 0.83
  Exp(λ=1.0): BF₁₀ = 8.2  log₁₀BF = 0.92
  Exp(λ=2.0): BF₁₀ = 6.8  log₁₀BF = 0.83
  Exp(λ=5.0): BF₁₀ = 2.7  log₁₀BF = 0.44

--- (d) Gamma priors ---
  Γ(α=0.5, β=0.5): BF₁₀ = 5.9  log₁₀BF = 0.77
  Γ(α=1, β=1): BF₁₀ = 8.2  log₁₀BF = 0.92
  Γ(α=2, β=1): BF₁₀ = 8.0  log₁₀BF = 0.90
  Γ(α=2, β=0.5): BF₁₀ = 3.6  log₁₀BF = 0.56
  Γ(α=5, β=2): BF₁₀ = 5.2  log₁₀BF = 0.72

======================================================================
PRIOR SENSITIVITY SUMMARY
======================================================================
  Prior range tested: 19 combinations across 4 families
  BF₁₀ range:  [2, 11]
  log₁₀BF range: [0.3, 1.1]
  Ratio max/min:  6×

  KEY FINDING: The Bayes factor varies by a factor of 6×
  across reasonable priors. At N=19, the Bayesian conclusion
  ("decisive" vs "strong" vs "moderate" evidence) depends
  primarily on the prior, not the data.
  This validates the paper's decision to present Bayesian results
  only as supplementary context, not as a primary argument.
